Comment: Specifies the version of the OntoZeolite ontology.

Target: OntoZeolite is an ontology developed for representing zeolitic materials

Comment: Indicates external ontologies that OntoZeolite may incorporate or reference.
Represents the general class of all species involved in the zeolite domain, including precursors and products.
Label: Species

Comment: Denotes the class related to the yield from zeolite synthesis processes, capturing efficiency and output.
Label: Yield

Comment: Citation information, for example, extracted from a bibtex file.
Label: Document

Comment: A data structure with components and units of measurements
Label: Measure Vector

Comment: An object to store a numerical value together with units of measurement. A class from OM-2 ontology.
Label: Measure

Comment: Collection of most common properties for crystal description, based on CIF standard.
Label: Crystal Information

Comment: One of the 255 zeolite frameworks known for now
Label: Zeolite Framework

Comment: Represents the materials that constitute zeolites, including their properties and structures.
Label: Zeolitic Material

Comment: The mass density (usually in g/cm3) of the material.
Label: Density

Comment: Information related to synthesis of a given zeolitic material
Label: Recipe

Comment: Chemical compound used for preparation of the final zeolite according to the recipe
Label: Precursor

Comment: A set of characteristics to describe the geometrical and/or topological properties of a material
Label: Topological Properties

Comment: The volume of cavities connected by channels, in %. Excluding izolated cavities. See also OccupiableVolume, AccessibleVolumePerCell
Label: Accessible Volume

Comment: The total volume of cavities in the crystal in %. See also AccessibleVolume, OccupiableVolumePerCell
Label: Occupiable Volume

Comment: Surface area of the cavities excluding isolated cavities in m^2/g. See also OccupiableAreaPerGram, AccessibleAreaPerCell, SpecificAccessibleArea.
Label: Accessible Area Per Gram

Comment: Total surface area of the cavities in m^2/g. See also AccessibleAreaPerGram, OccupiableAreaPerCell, SpecificOccupiableArea
Label: Occupiable Area Per Gram

Comment: The volume of cavities connected by channels, in A^3 per crystal unit cell. Excluding izolated cavities. See also OccupiableVolumePerCell, AccessibleVolume
Label: Accessible Volume Per Cell

Comment: The total volume of cavities in the crystal in A^3 per crystal unit cell. See also AccessibleVolumePerCell, OccupiableVolume
Label: Occupiable Volume Per Cell

Comment: Surface area of the cavities excluding isolated cavities in A^2 per crystal unit cell. See also OccupiableAreaPerCell, AccessibleAreaPerGram, SpecificAccessibleArea.
Label: Accessible Area Per Cell

Comment: Total surface area of the cavities in A^2 per crystal unit cell. See also AccessibleAreaPerCell, OccupiableAreaPerGram, SpecificOccupiableArea
Label: Occupiable Area Per Cell

Comment: Surface area of the cavities excluding isolated cavities in m^2/cm^3. See also SpecificOccupiableArea, AccessibleAreaPerCell, AccessibleAreaPerGram.
Label: Specific Accessible Area

Comment: Total surface area of the cavities in m^2/cm^3. See also SpecificAccessibleArea, OccupiableAreaPerGram, OccupiableAreaPerCell
Label: Specific Occupiable Area

Comment: Characteristics of porocity. Diameter of the biggest sphere to move along a channel or to reside in a cavity. One of topological properties
Label: Sphere Diameter

Comment: Topological building unit (BU) to describe the structure of the crystal. Obsolete since 2007. See also CompositeBU
Label: Secondary BU

Comment: An array of 10 or 12 numbers
Label: Coordination Sequence

Comment: Size and count of the smallest rings associated with 6 angles of T-atom. Each T-atom contains 6 values.
Label: Vertex Symbol

Comment: Links a ZeoliteMaterial to its structural framework, characterizing its molecular architecture.
Label: has Zeolitic Material

Comment: Links the material to its density.
Label: has Density

Comment: Connection of the crystal entity to CrystalInformation containing the crystallographic data
Label: has Crystal Information

Comment: Associates a Zeolite with its Recipe, detailing the synthesis process.
Label: has Recipe

Comment: Connects a Recipe to its Precursor(s), defining the starting materials required for zeolite synthesis.
Label: has Precursor

Comment: Links the material to its topological properties
Label: has Topological Properties

Comment: Links the topological property to the Accessible volume
Label: has Accessible Volume

Comment: Links the topological property to the Occupiable volume
Label: has Occupiable Volume

Comment: Links the topological property to the AccessibleAreaPerGram
Label: has Accessible Area Per Gram

Comment: Links the topological property to the Occupiable volume
Label: has Occupiable Area Per Gram

Comment: Links the topological property to the OccupiableAreaPerGram
Label: has Accessible Volume Per Cell

Comment: Links the topological property to the OccupiableVolumePerCell
Label: has Occupiable Volume Per Cell

Comment: Links the topological property to the AccessibleAreaPerCell
Label: has Accessible Area Per Cell

Comment: Links the topological property to the OccupiableAreaPerCell
Label: has Occupiable Area Per Cell

Comment: Links the topological property to the SpecificAccessibleArea
Label: has Specific Accessible Area

Comment: Links the topological property to the SpecificOccupiableArea
Label: has Specific Occupiable Area

Comment: Links the topological property to its porocity characteristics
Label: has Sphere Diameter

Comment: Links the topological property to its SecondaryBU. There may be multiple BU
Label: has Secondary BU

Comment: Boolean property indicating if a ZeoliteFramework is structurally interrupted.
Label: is Interrupted

Comment: Boolean property indicating if a ZeoliteFramework has intergrowth with other structures.
Label: is Intergrowth

Comment: For simple frameworks a 3-letter code, for interrupted or intergrowth a more complex code
Label: has Framework Code

Comment: Boolean property indicating if a ZeoliteFramework is hypothetic.
Label: Is Hypothetic

Comment: The material used as a reference for studying the framework properties
Label: is Reference Zeolite

Comment: Chemical formula in a string format
Label: has Chemical Formula

Comment: Details the steps involved in the preparation of a batch for zeolite synthesis.
Label: has Batch Preparation

Comment: Describes the process and efficiency of recovering the final zeolite product post-synthesis.
Label: has Product Recovery

Comment: Captures information on the crystallization phase in the zeolite synthesis recipe.
Label: has Crystallization

Comment: Allows for additional annotations or remarks pertinent to the synthesis recipe of a zeolite.
Label: has Notes

Comment: Describes the chemical composition of a recipe for zeolite synthesis.
Label: has Composition

Comment: Specifies the composition of the initial batch used in a zeolite synthesis recipe.
Label: has Batch Composition

Comment: Human-readable description of the characterization procedure
Label: has Characterization

Comment: Human-readable description of the characterization procedure
Label: has Source Material
